1
00:00:01,668 --> 00:00:04,713
[brazen music playing]

2
00:00:10,969 --> 00:00:15,682
[electronic blipping]

3
00:00:15,765 --> 00:00:17,559
[Red, in English]
<i>You're gonna love this place.</i>

4
00:00:17,642 --> 00:00:20,270
[Red, in English] <i>It's a, uh,</i>
<i>battle of mini gladiators.</i>

5
00:00:20,353 --> 00:00:22,647
- [thuds]
- [crowd gasps, whistles]

6
00:00:22,731 --> 00:00:24,023
[in English] Finish her!

7
00:00:25,066 --> 00:00:26,151
[in English] Finish her now!

8
00:00:26,234 --> 00:00:27,235
[crowd gasps, whistles]

9
00:00:27,318 --> 00:00:28,903
PREVIOUSLY

10
00:00:28,987 --> 00:00:30,780
[Vladimir in English]
<i>If you can give me Amazing Ame,</i>

11
00:00:30,864 --> 00:00:33,366
<i>I will promise you</i>
<i>it'll be worth your while.</i>

12
00:00:33,450 --> 00:00:34,367
[woman] <i>Is there a problem?</i>

13
00:00:34,451 --> 00:00:35,452
[patron] <i>Someone took my jacket.</i>

14
00:00:35,535 --> 00:00:37,912
There's a Rolex in the pocket. Goddammit!

15
00:00:37,996 --> 00:00:38,872
[Mongki] <i>Do you know Atoy?</i>

16
00:00:38,955 --> 00:00:39,914
[Bunda] Well, this is--

17
00:00:39,998 --> 00:00:41,291
- [thuds]
- [screaming]

18
00:00:42,041 --> 00:00:43,501
[MC] <i>You have another fight, Ame.</i>

19
00:00:43,585 --> 00:00:44,919
Who's my opponent?

20
00:00:45,003 --> 00:00:47,172
There, Darryl.

21
00:00:47,756 --> 00:00:49,257
[security] <i>It's chaos out there.</i>

22
00:00:49,340 --> 00:00:51,259
<i>Looks like the new janitor</i>

23
00:00:51,342 --> 00:00:53,303
<i>accused of stealing</i>
<i>from a customer escaped.</i>

24
00:00:53,386 --> 00:00:55,722
[vendor] With so many of them there,
he still escaped?

25
00:00:55,805 --> 00:00:57,140
This suits me.

26
00:00:57,223 --> 00:00:58,391
[clicking and clacking]

27
00:00:58,475 --> 00:01:00,477
[Ibyang] What's this? Bat cave?

28
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:03,188
[Mongki] <i>I'm only looking</i>
<i>for one person here! Atoy!</i>

29
00:01:03,938 --> 00:01:05,815
So, if you don't want
to get dragged into this,

30
00:01:05,899 --> 00:01:07,525
just answer me!

31
00:01:08,193 --> 00:01:10,612
The person you're looking for
isn't here anymore.

32
00:01:10,695 --> 00:01:13,615
- Do you know those people?
- [Cita] <i>I heard one of their names.</i>

33
00:01:13,698 --> 00:01:15,158
[Cita] Mongki?

34
00:01:15,241 --> 00:01:17,535
[Tonet] <i>I really can't find Ibyang.</i>

35
00:01:17,619 --> 00:01:19,829
- Not in the kitchen or the CR.
- [Cita] Huh?

36
00:01:21,414 --> 00:01:25,502
- [clicking and clacking]
- [electronic blipping]

37
00:01:27,504 --> 00:01:29,756
[mysterious music playing]

38
00:01:30,507 --> 00:01:32,467
Son of a thread!

39
00:01:32,550 --> 00:01:33,676
Psst! Hey!

40
00:01:34,427 --> 00:01:36,888
[mischievous music playing]

41
00:01:38,181 --> 00:01:41,476
- What are you doing here?
- Ah, Master Grumpy. [yawns]

42
00:01:42,018 --> 00:01:43,102
Huh?

43
00:01:43,603 --> 00:01:44,729
- Ah, sorry.
- [mutters]

44
00:01:46,189 --> 00:01:49,067
I accidentally pulled something.

45
00:01:49,150 --> 00:01:51,069
Then I couldn't get out.

46
00:01:52,278 --> 00:01:55,615
You really love meddling
with things that aren't yours, huh?

47
00:01:55,698 --> 00:01:57,617
Hey, I behaved!

48
00:01:57,700 --> 00:01:59,035
Oh, really?

49
00:01:59,119 --> 00:02:00,745
So, what's this?

50
00:02:01,621 --> 00:02:03,081
Huh? What's this?

51
00:02:04,415 --> 00:02:05,917
[whimsical music playing]

52
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:07,502
Well…

53
00:02:08,878 --> 00:02:09,838
Um…

54
00:02:09,921 --> 00:02:14,592
I got bored, so I tried on that wig.

55
00:02:15,552 --> 00:02:18,012
Then I couldn't get out.

56
00:02:18,096 --> 00:02:20,765
Good thing that's all I played with.

57
00:02:20,849 --> 00:02:23,268
I saw there are stick pins there.

58
00:02:24,435 --> 00:02:25,520
[in English] Wow!

59
00:02:26,020 --> 00:02:27,105
Thanks for that.

60
00:02:27,188 --> 00:02:29,190
What if you got hurt?

61
00:02:29,274 --> 00:02:30,859
[whimsical music continues]

62
00:02:30,942 --> 00:02:34,821
Why do you hide things like this here?

63
00:02:34,904 --> 00:02:36,489
That's why they're hidden, right?

64
00:02:36,573 --> 00:02:38,116
So, no one tinkers with them.

65
00:02:38,700 --> 00:02:41,244
But what are these for?

66
00:02:41,327 --> 00:02:42,287
[snipping]

67
00:02:42,370 --> 00:02:44,956
Did you sew all this?

68
00:02:45,832 --> 00:02:47,750
And it looks so nice inside.

69
00:02:48,334 --> 00:02:50,128
Cool!

70
00:02:51,462 --> 00:02:54,465
- Unlike outside, it's ugly!
- [scoffs]

71
00:02:54,549 --> 00:02:56,551
You have money.

72
00:02:56,634 --> 00:02:58,052
Why don't you fix the shop?

73
00:02:59,095 --> 00:03:01,973
So that it looks as good as this!

74
00:03:03,558 --> 00:03:06,102
[whimsical music concludes]

75
00:03:06,185 --> 00:03:07,478
[exhales]

76
00:03:08,771 --> 00:03:09,981
Ibyang,

77
00:03:10,064 --> 00:03:13,610
first of all, no one should enter here.

78
00:03:13,693 --> 00:03:15,194
Just me, okay?

79
00:03:15,278 --> 00:03:18,197
Second, I shouldn't answer your questions.

80
00:03:18,281 --> 00:03:20,033
I have no obligation
to answer your questions.

81
00:03:20,116 --> 00:03:24,579
Promise me you won't tell anyone
you saw this room.

82
00:03:25,538 --> 00:03:30,627
- Do you understand? Mm.
- Uh-huh. So, it's like…

83
00:03:31,336 --> 00:03:33,379
our secret?

84
00:03:34,005 --> 00:03:35,798
What secret? No!

85
00:03:35,882 --> 00:03:37,592
Just don't tell anyone.

86
00:03:37,675 --> 00:03:38,635
You didn't see this.

87
00:03:38,718 --> 00:03:40,011
You didn't enter it.

88
00:03:40,094 --> 00:03:41,179
Clear?

89
00:03:41,971 --> 00:03:45,266
[mischievous music playing]

90
00:03:46,267 --> 00:03:47,644
Ah, fine, if you want,

91
00:03:47,727 --> 00:03:49,020
I won't look for Ame anymore.

92
00:03:49,103 --> 00:03:50,647
I can stop looking.

93
00:03:50,730 --> 00:03:52,815
Oh, no, no.

94
00:03:52,899 --> 00:03:54,192
Promise!

95
00:03:54,275 --> 00:03:55,860
You can't take a joke.

96
00:03:55,944 --> 00:03:59,822
Just save my Big Sister Ame,

97
00:04:00,698 --> 00:04:04,410
and I'll forget everything about you.

98
00:04:04,494 --> 00:04:05,328
Mmm-hmm.

99
00:04:05,411 --> 00:04:07,664
- Even this room.
- Mmm-hmm.

100
00:04:08,665 --> 00:04:12,293
Like I have amnesia.

101
00:04:12,377 --> 00:04:13,795
Ah, amnesia.

102
00:04:13,878 --> 00:04:14,837
You're sure about that, huh.

103
00:04:14,921 --> 00:04:19,384
And we'll never see
each other again, ever!

104
00:04:20,093 --> 00:04:21,261
Mmm-hmm.

105
00:04:21,344 --> 00:04:22,512
Okay.

106
00:04:22,595 --> 00:04:25,848
[upbeat music playing]

107
00:04:26,766 --> 00:04:30,103
[suave music playing]

108
00:04:33,606 --> 00:04:34,482
[sewing machine whirring]

109
00:04:34,565 --> 00:04:35,441
[swishing]

110
00:04:35,525 --> 00:04:36,401
[snipping]

111
00:04:37,527 --> 00:04:38,945
[sewing machine whirring]

112
00:04:39,988 --> 00:04:41,322
[sewing machine whirring]

113
00:04:41,406 --> 00:04:42,699
[gun cocks]

114
00:04:43,199 --> 00:04:44,701
[gun firing]

115
00:04:44,784 --> 00:04:46,119
[clicking]

116
00:04:47,078 --> 00:04:48,413
[snips]

117
00:04:50,498 --> 00:04:52,792
[electronic blipping]

118
00:04:56,337 --> 00:04:57,797
[crowd cheering]

119
00:04:57,880 --> 00:04:59,549
Shake hands, shake hands,
shake hands, shake hands!

120
00:04:59,632 --> 00:05:01,050
[crowd cheering]

121
00:05:01,134 --> 00:05:02,760
‪[energetic club music playing]

122
00:05:02,844 --> 00:05:04,053
Let's get it on! Box!

123
00:05:04,137 --> 00:05:06,180
- [bell dings]
- [crowd cheering]

124
00:05:07,098 --> 00:05:08,182
Go ahead, Darryl.

125
00:05:08,266 --> 00:05:09,475
Beat me.

126
00:05:09,559 --> 00:05:11,227
Do this for your father.

127
00:05:11,311 --> 00:05:13,438
[crowd cheering]

128
00:05:13,521 --> 00:05:14,731
[in English] Pound!

129
00:05:14,814 --> 00:05:16,399
[crowd cheering]

130
00:05:16,899 --> 00:05:18,860
[Darryl] You need this win more.

131
00:05:19,527 --> 00:05:20,570
For Ibyang.

132
00:05:23,114 --> 00:05:25,325
Oh, oh, what's that?!

133
00:05:25,408 --> 00:05:27,452
Listen, Ame.

134
00:05:28,036 --> 00:05:29,912
If the people get mad at us,

135
00:05:31,247 --> 00:05:33,541
we'll both be in trouble.

136
00:05:33,624 --> 00:05:35,168
We have no choice.

137
00:05:35,251 --> 00:05:37,295
We need to fight.

138
00:05:37,378 --> 00:05:41,049
So, beat me because you're closer
to getting out of here.

139
00:05:41,132 --> 00:05:42,383
Don't waste it.

140
00:05:43,134 --> 00:05:45,762
- [crowd cheering]
- [shouts]

141
00:05:52,393 --> 00:05:53,686
[man, in English] Fight, fight, fight!

142
00:05:55,063 --> 00:05:56,522
- [in English] Did you see that hit?
- Yup!

143
00:05:56,606 --> 00:05:57,607
[crowd cheering]

144
00:05:57,690 --> 00:05:59,484
[thudding]

145
00:06:03,404 --> 00:06:05,198
[bell dings]

146
00:06:05,281 --> 00:06:07,992
[crowd cheering]

147
00:06:08,076 --> 00:06:12,246
[in English] Three, four, five, six,

148
00:06:12,955 --> 00:06:17,210
seven, eight, nine, ten!

149
00:06:18,753 --> 00:06:22,298
[crowd cheering]

150
00:06:28,805 --> 00:06:30,515
You weren't answering!

151
00:06:30,598 --> 00:06:32,600
[uneasy music playing]

152
00:06:32,683 --> 00:06:34,977
Sorry. Just busy.

153
00:06:35,061 --> 00:06:36,229
[Mongki scoffs]

154
00:06:36,312 --> 00:06:37,772
Where did Atoy move?

155
00:06:37,855 --> 00:06:38,815
Huh?

156
00:06:40,650 --> 00:06:43,277
Atoy's been gone a long time.

157
00:06:43,361 --> 00:06:46,239
And the people here don't know anything!

158
00:06:46,322 --> 00:06:48,825
So, please, stop scaring them.

159
00:06:48,908 --> 00:06:51,160
[uneasy music continues]

160
00:06:53,287 --> 00:06:54,622
I'll fix this.

161
00:06:55,665 --> 00:06:57,458
- You just caused trouble.
- [sharp inhale]

162
00:07:00,211 --> 00:07:01,045
‪[sharp inhale]

163
00:07:03,256 --> 00:07:05,508
You've already got your tenth win.

164
00:07:06,050 --> 00:07:07,468
You can leave now.

165
00:07:08,553 --> 00:07:10,680
I hope they really mean it.

166
00:07:11,389 --> 00:07:13,099
[somber music playing]

167
00:07:13,182 --> 00:07:15,226
I'll tell the stage manager,

168
00:07:15,893 --> 00:07:17,895
I'll leave tomorrow instead.

169
00:07:17,979 --> 00:07:19,689
I'll go with you.

170
00:07:20,898 --> 00:07:24,735
Are you sure?
They'll make you fight again tomorrow!

171
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:27,989
Then I'll fight.

172
00:07:28,072 --> 00:07:29,365
I'm used to it.

173
00:07:31,951 --> 00:07:33,244
Hey, Darryl?

174
00:07:33,327 --> 00:07:35,037
Are you going insane?

175
00:07:35,121 --> 00:07:37,165
If I leave now,

176
00:07:37,248 --> 00:07:39,333
who will take care of you?

177
00:07:39,417 --> 00:07:41,461
[sentimental music playing]

178
00:07:42,044 --> 00:07:44,088
[teasing]

179
00:07:45,631 --> 00:07:47,258
[door clicks open]

180
00:07:48,217 --> 00:07:51,304
Ame. Ma'am Lorna is calling you.

181
00:07:51,387 --> 00:07:54,849
There's a big-time customer
who wants to meet you.

182
00:07:55,433 --> 00:07:56,726
Get ready, hurry.

183
00:07:56,809 --> 00:08:00,646
[brooding music playing]

184
00:08:05,067 --> 00:08:07,820
You shouldn't have paid
those people, Gavin.

185
00:08:07,904 --> 00:08:10,031
You started it. You didn't even apologize.

186
00:08:10,114 --> 00:08:12,074
Why would I do that?

187
00:08:18,206 --> 00:08:22,001
So, Mongki, what kind of trouble
did you drag my son into this time?

188
00:08:22,084 --> 00:08:23,252
It's okay, Mom.

189
00:08:23,336 --> 00:08:24,670
I already made peace.

190
00:08:25,463 --> 00:08:27,006
[in English] No, Gavin.

191
00:08:27,089 --> 00:08:29,133
[in English] I want
to hear it from this man.

192
00:08:29,217 --> 00:08:31,427
In Tabang Lupa, ma'am.

193
00:08:31,511 --> 00:08:34,180
We were just going to collect payment,

194
00:08:34,263 --> 00:08:35,806
then suddenly, chaos broke out.

195
00:08:35,890 --> 00:08:37,725
But Gavin wasn't hurt.

196
00:08:38,351 --> 00:08:41,187
What business did you have there, huh?

197
00:08:41,270 --> 00:08:44,732
I already told you, Mom, didn't I?
We went there to play basketball.

198
00:08:45,650 --> 00:08:48,611
[in English] We have a really, really
nice basketball court in the clubhouse.

199
00:08:48,694 --> 00:08:50,696
And then you go wandering everywhere!

200
00:08:50,780 --> 00:08:52,990
You should have just gone with your dad.

201
00:08:53,074 --> 00:08:55,368
He's giving the foreign visitors a tour.

202
00:08:57,119 --> 00:08:59,622
I don't want to be involved
in whatever Dad is doing.

203
00:08:59,705 --> 00:09:02,583
I'm different! And I don't
want to be like him.

204
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:05,586
[in English] Gavin, why are you
like that towards your father?

205
00:09:06,254 --> 00:09:07,088
Gavin--

206
00:09:07,171 --> 00:09:09,257
[in English] I'm still
talking to you, Gavin!

207
00:09:09,340 --> 00:09:10,841
Ga--

208
00:09:10,925 --> 00:09:12,885
[somber music playing]

209
00:09:12,969 --> 00:09:14,053
[in English] What a night, my friend.

210
00:09:14,136 --> 00:09:15,137
[in English] I know, I know.

211
00:09:15,221 --> 00:09:17,473
[in English] I told you,
you're gonna enjoy this night, right?

212
00:09:17,557 --> 00:09:18,683
- [chuckles]
- [in English] Indeed.

213
00:09:18,766 --> 00:09:20,476
[Red, in English] Hey, there she is.

214
00:09:23,521 --> 00:09:26,649
[Lorna, in English] Ame,
this is Sir Vladimir.

215
00:09:26,732 --> 00:09:29,068
[in English] Sir, the Amazing Ame!

216
00:09:29,735 --> 00:09:31,571
[in English] You are so amazing!

217
00:09:32,113 --> 00:09:33,364
[in English] Can I take a picture, please?

218
00:09:33,447 --> 00:09:35,491
[in English] Come, come, come, come here.

219
00:09:35,575 --> 00:09:36,701
[in English] Come, come, come!

220
00:09:37,285 --> 00:09:38,536
[camera shutter clicking]

221
00:09:38,619 --> 00:09:40,121
Ooh!

222
00:09:40,204 --> 00:09:41,205
Mmm!

223
00:09:41,289 --> 00:09:42,582
- [chuckles]
- [in English] Oh, yes!

224
00:09:43,291 --> 00:09:45,751
[in English] Did you know that
I am the top-tier agent

225
00:09:45,835 --> 00:09:48,504
here in the whole of Asia?

226
00:09:48,588 --> 00:09:50,631
[in English] Do you understand
what I'm saying?

227
00:09:50,715 --> 00:09:51,716
[in English] Yes, sir.

228
00:09:51,799 --> 00:09:52,675
[in English] Perfect!

229
00:09:52,758 --> 00:09:56,971
[in English] Because I have a client
in Japan, and he will absolutely love you!

230
00:09:57,805 --> 00:09:59,640
[in English] All you have to do
is make him happy,

231
00:09:59,724 --> 00:10:02,476
- and he will change your life!
- [laughs]

232
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:03,894
- What?
- [in English] Yes!

233
00:10:04,562 --> 00:10:06,856
He said he has a client in Japan.

234
00:10:06,939 --> 00:10:08,357
Make him happy.

235
00:10:08,441 --> 00:10:10,526
Your life will change, right?

236
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:12,486
- Change--
- I know.

237
00:10:12,570 --> 00:10:14,739
But that's not the deal.

238
00:10:15,239 --> 00:10:16,949
I need to get out of here.

239
00:10:17,033 --> 00:10:19,076
There's a child waiting for me!

240
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:21,412
[in English] What… What is she saying?

241
00:10:21,495 --> 00:10:22,413
[in English] I said, no.

242
00:10:22,496 --> 00:10:24,498
[in English] I want out.
Someone is waiting for me.

243
00:10:24,582 --> 00:10:26,626
[in English] Oh… Oh, no, don't you worry.

244
00:10:26,709 --> 00:10:28,419
[stammers] I will take care of you.

245
00:10:28,502 --> 00:10:29,378
[in English] It's okay, it's okay.

246
00:10:29,462 --> 00:10:30,796
[in English] You can come with us.

247
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:32,006
[in English] Let's take more pictures.

248
00:10:32,089 --> 00:10:35,468
[in English] I will show this
to my… my client in Japan. Here we go.

249
00:10:35,551 --> 00:10:36,761
[mutters] Right here.

250
00:10:36,844 --> 00:10:37,762
[in English] Yes.

251
00:10:37,845 --> 00:10:39,221
[camera shutter clicking]

252
00:10:39,305 --> 00:10:41,807
[in English] He will be so happy
to meet you.

253
00:10:42,391 --> 00:10:43,267
- [in English] It's okay.
- [Ame crying]

254
00:10:43,351 --> 00:10:46,437
[in English] Don't… You don't have to cry.
Come here, come here…

255
00:10:46,520 --> 00:10:48,773
[in English] Don't cry. It's okay.

256
00:10:48,856 --> 00:10:50,524
- [sobbing]
- [somber music playing]

257
00:10:50,608 --> 00:10:52,360
[in English] The Amazing Ame!

258
00:10:54,236 --> 00:10:56,238
[in English] He will be very, very happy.

259
00:10:56,322 --> 00:10:57,323
[in English] It's okay.

260
00:11:01,452 --> 00:11:03,079
‪[melancholic music playing]

261
00:11:20,054 --> 00:11:22,264
They probably won't come back anymore.

262
00:11:22,348 --> 00:11:26,018
We told them that you already
left this town.

263
00:11:30,606 --> 00:11:33,442
How's your search for her Big Sister Ame?

264
00:11:35,653 --> 00:11:37,696
Don't mention it to Ibyang.

265
00:11:38,823 --> 00:11:39,782
Oh?

266
00:11:40,449 --> 00:11:41,659
Why, Atoy?

267
00:11:41,742 --> 00:11:42,952
It's dangerous.

268
00:11:43,661 --> 00:11:46,580
Looks like Ame was forced
into underground fighting.

269
00:11:46,664 --> 00:11:47,665
What?!

270
00:11:47,748 --> 00:11:49,166
[in English] Underground fighting?

271
00:11:49,250 --> 00:11:50,334
Poor woman.

272
00:11:50,418 --> 00:11:51,293
[Atoy] Exactly.

273
00:11:52,336 --> 00:11:54,046
But don't worry.

274
00:11:55,297 --> 00:11:57,299
I already have a way to get inside.

275
00:11:58,050 --> 00:12:01,804
Ma'am, where did you buy this dumpling?

276
00:12:02,596 --> 00:12:03,514
It's delicious!

277
00:12:04,348 --> 00:12:07,435
Atoy bought that for you.

278
00:12:08,269 --> 00:12:09,228
Oh?

279
00:12:09,311 --> 00:12:10,479
Oh, it's salty! [spits]

280
00:12:10,563 --> 00:12:11,772
[quirky music playing]

281
00:12:11,856 --> 00:12:12,898
[Ibyang] It's salty!

282
00:12:12,982 --> 00:12:13,941
Salty?

283
00:12:14,024 --> 00:12:15,860
But you almost finished it.

284
00:12:15,943 --> 00:12:16,819
Still salty.

285
00:12:16,902 --> 00:12:20,448
[quirky music continues]

286
00:12:20,531 --> 00:12:22,241
[door clicks open]

287
00:12:28,998 --> 00:12:35,129
[somber music playing]

288
00:12:40,092 --> 00:12:41,886
What happened, Ame?

289
00:12:42,928 --> 00:12:45,848
I bet you already have a No. 1 fan, right?

290
00:12:46,932 --> 00:12:50,060
That's good. It'll be easier
for you to get out.

291
00:12:52,313 --> 00:12:53,230
Ame?

292
00:12:55,733 --> 00:12:58,110
A client talked to me.

293
00:12:59,487 --> 00:13:03,199
He said he wants to take me
to Japan for his customer.

294
00:13:04,033 --> 00:13:05,284
Why?

295
00:13:05,367 --> 00:13:06,535
For what?

296
00:13:07,203 --> 00:13:08,871
I don't even know.

297
00:13:12,291 --> 00:13:14,293
But I have a bad feeling about it.

298
00:13:16,003 --> 00:13:18,756
[somber music continues]

299
00:13:19,423 --> 00:13:21,133
Papa Jesus,

300
00:13:22,510 --> 00:13:27,056
I know Big Sister Ame and I are naughty.

301
00:13:29,725 --> 00:13:33,020
It's just hard to earn money nowadays.

302
00:13:33,103 --> 00:13:35,648
[rain pattering]

303
00:13:35,731 --> 00:13:38,234
But I promise, Brother Jesus,

304
00:13:39,818 --> 00:13:46,283
just bring Sis Ame back to me,
and I'll really be good.

305
00:13:49,787 --> 00:13:52,623
I don't want to stay here
anymore, Brother Jesus!

306
00:13:55,125 --> 00:13:58,712
Please, just bring Sis Ame back to me,

307
00:13:59,838 --> 00:14:02,967
so I can leave Master Grumpy behind.

308
00:14:03,968 --> 00:14:06,387
[melancholic music playing]

309
00:14:06,470 --> 00:14:10,891
That's it, Brother Jesus.

310
00:14:10,975 --> 00:14:12,726
That's our deal, okay?

311
00:14:16,272 --> 00:14:17,690
Amen.

312
00:14:18,482 --> 00:14:20,943
[thunder rumbles]

313
00:14:21,026 --> 00:14:23,737
[melancholic music continues]

314
00:14:32,788 --> 00:14:34,039
Are you okay?

315
00:14:34,582 --> 00:14:35,958
[thunder rumbles]

316
00:14:36,041 --> 00:14:40,504
Looks like these lightning strikes
are strong, and there's a storm brewing.

317
00:14:40,588 --> 00:14:42,006
If you want,

318
00:14:42,756 --> 00:14:44,592
I can stay with you here?

319
00:14:45,217 --> 00:14:46,802
No, I'm fine.

320
00:14:46,886 --> 00:14:49,221
What do you think of me, a coward?

321
00:14:50,097 --> 00:14:52,182
[gentle music playing]

322
00:14:52,266 --> 00:14:57,229
Okay then… Are you sure?

323
00:15:00,816 --> 00:15:02,526
Yes. Yes, of course.

324
00:15:02,610 --> 00:15:03,777
Yes, of course.

325
00:15:03,861 --> 00:15:05,613
[thunder rumbling]

326
00:15:05,696 --> 00:15:09,366
Well, if you need anything,

327
00:15:09,450 --> 00:15:11,118
I'll leave the door open.

328
00:15:11,827 --> 00:15:15,831
If you really need me, just shout.
Or come to me, knock on my room.

329
00:15:15,915 --> 00:15:17,082
Are you okay?

330
00:15:17,166 --> 00:15:18,208
Hmm.

331
00:15:18,292 --> 00:15:19,585
Are you sure?

332
00:15:19,668 --> 00:15:20,794
Hmm.

333
00:15:22,046 --> 00:15:23,422
[in English] Final answer?

334
00:15:24,256 --> 00:15:26,759
[gentle music continues]

335
00:15:26,842 --> 00:15:28,636
You're not scared?

336
00:15:30,054 --> 00:15:31,055
No.

337
00:15:31,138 --> 00:15:34,183
[gentle music continues]

338
00:15:36,936 --> 00:15:39,563
Just remember, if you need anything,
just call out.

339
00:15:39,647 --> 00:15:42,566
Say, "Master Grumpy!"

340
00:15:45,903 --> 00:15:49,281
[thunder rumbling]

341
00:15:50,741 --> 00:15:56,747
[gentle music continues]

342
00:15:56,830 --> 00:15:58,123
OPEN
PLEASE COME IN!

343
00:16:02,836 --> 00:16:05,130
[thunder rumbling]

344
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:12,805
Do you know them?

345
00:16:14,098 --> 00:16:15,140
Who?

346
00:16:15,933 --> 00:16:17,184
Those fools.

347
00:16:17,267 --> 00:16:20,312
[inquisitive music playing]

348
00:16:20,396 --> 00:16:21,438
No.

349
00:16:22,439 --> 00:16:24,483
Why would I know them?

350
00:16:26,694 --> 00:16:29,822
What about that rich kid?

351
00:16:31,824 --> 00:16:32,908
No, why?

352
00:16:34,910 --> 00:16:36,203
Nothing, nothing.

353
00:16:37,037 --> 00:16:38,414
It's just a shame…

354
00:16:40,374 --> 00:16:43,210
I thought we already won.

355
00:16:43,293 --> 00:16:45,963
I thought we could collect,
but turns out we lost again.

356
00:16:46,463 --> 00:16:48,382
My wallet's gone!

357
00:16:49,216 --> 00:16:51,969
Yes, maybe someone swiped it
during the commotion.

358
00:16:53,345 --> 00:16:56,557
Why would anyone steal your wallet?

359
00:16:58,017 --> 00:16:59,435
Cap, come on.

360
00:17:00,394 --> 00:17:03,063
You're the only one who's loaded here.

361
00:17:03,147 --> 00:17:04,857
[scoffs] Cap.

362
00:17:04,940 --> 00:17:06,316
As a fatter of mact,

363
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:08,444
I had 10,000 pesos in that wallet.

364
00:17:08,527 --> 00:17:12,740
And I had some pictures that I kept there.

365
00:17:12,823 --> 00:17:14,825
Maybe it's a scandal, brother, huh?

366
00:17:15,743 --> 00:17:16,869
No.

367
00:17:19,079 --> 00:17:21,206
No, no, no.

368
00:17:21,290 --> 00:17:23,709
Not at all. And Father stiffed me.

369
00:17:24,460 --> 00:17:28,922
He didn't give me my share.

370
00:17:29,006 --> 00:17:33,886
Cap, come on, look at me.
As if I had anything hidden there.

371
00:17:35,387 --> 00:17:38,724
[mischievous music playing]

372
00:17:39,433 --> 00:17:40,726
All twenties.

373
00:17:40,809 --> 00:17:43,062
[thunder rumbles]

374
00:17:44,188 --> 00:17:48,817
[sentimental music playing]

375
00:17:50,194 --> 00:17:52,029
I look cute here.

376
00:17:52,696 --> 00:17:53,781
Now, beautiful.

377
00:17:55,282 --> 00:17:56,909
REPUBLIC OF THE PHILIPPINES
NATIONAL IDENTITY

378
00:17:56,992 --> 00:17:58,368
[sentimental music continues]

379
00:17:58,452 --> 00:18:01,914
I thought you already forgot me, brother.

380
00:18:01,997 --> 00:18:05,167
[sentimental music continues]

381
00:18:09,046 --> 00:18:12,883
- [thunder rumbles]
- [sentimental music continues]

382
00:18:19,515 --> 00:18:20,933
[sighs]

383
00:18:25,854 --> 00:18:27,773
[sentimental music continues]

384
00:18:35,447 --> 00:18:36,448
[sobs]

385
00:18:41,078 --> 00:18:45,415
[sobbing]

386
00:18:55,342 --> 00:18:56,635
[door clicks open]

387
00:18:57,511 --> 00:18:58,470
Hey!

388
00:18:59,096 --> 00:19:00,639
Oh!

389
00:19:00,722 --> 00:19:01,932
- 'Nang.
- [Cita] Oh?

390
00:19:02,558 --> 00:19:04,810
- [grunts]
- [Cita] You slept here?

391
00:19:05,686 --> 00:19:07,229
Yes, Mom ‘Nang.

392
00:19:07,312 --> 00:19:10,065
Uh… Yes, ‘Nang.

393
00:19:10,149 --> 00:19:11,525
I just stayed with this kid

394
00:19:11,608 --> 00:19:15,028
because the lightning
was strong last night.

395
00:19:17,322 --> 00:19:19,074
You did the right thing.

396
00:19:19,158 --> 00:19:22,035
I knew it, your heart
would turn mellow for Ibyang.

397
00:19:22,953 --> 00:19:23,829
Coffee, ‘Nang?

398
00:19:23,912 --> 00:19:24,997
Sure, sure.

399
00:19:25,706 --> 00:19:26,999
Since you offered.

400
00:19:27,583 --> 00:19:28,834
[chuckles]

401
00:19:31,587 --> 00:19:32,838
[T-bak sighs]

402
00:19:32,921 --> 00:19:33,922
[T-bak] Mmm.

403
00:19:34,464 --> 00:19:35,507
[Emerson] What's this?

404
00:19:36,508 --> 00:19:39,219
Nice. Nice. What's this, trash?

405
00:19:41,972 --> 00:19:43,891
I knew it!

406
00:19:45,475 --> 00:19:46,518
[grunts in frustration]

407
00:19:46,602 --> 00:19:47,561
Hmm?

408
00:19:49,188 --> 00:19:50,814
This is my wallet!

409
00:19:51,440 --> 00:19:54,693
[gentle music playing]

410
00:19:56,403 --> 00:19:57,571
‪[indistinct chattering]

411
00:20:03,118 --> 00:20:04,411
Otap?

412
00:20:10,209 --> 00:20:11,501
- T-bak!
- Hm? Hey!

413
00:20:12,753 --> 00:20:14,129
Did you see who brought this?

414
00:20:14,213 --> 00:20:15,631
That?

415
00:20:15,714 --> 00:20:18,550
That came from Brother Atoy's assistant!

416
00:20:20,135 --> 00:20:23,805
[gentle music continues]

417
00:20:26,683 --> 00:20:27,893
[Emerson] Atoy?

418
00:20:27,976 --> 00:20:29,269
[gasping]

419
00:20:29,353 --> 00:20:30,938
- [Tonet] Oh…
- [Emerson] Atoy?

420
00:20:31,438 --> 00:20:36,777
- [gasps]
- [Emerson] Atoy. A-- Sis?

421
00:20:36,860 --> 00:20:38,237
[clears throat]

422
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:39,446
[in English] Good morning.

423
00:20:39,529 --> 00:20:42,115
Uh, are you Atoy's assistant?

424
00:20:42,199 --> 00:20:43,116
[Tonet gasps]

425
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:44,034
[Tonet clears throat]

426
00:20:44,117 --> 00:20:47,037
[in soft voice] Ah, no, I don't know him.

427
00:20:47,120 --> 00:20:48,705
Who is he?

428
00:20:48,789 --> 00:20:53,460
Ah. No, I thought you were
the one who returned my wallet.

429
00:20:54,253 --> 00:20:56,213
Uh, please say thank you.

430
00:20:56,296 --> 00:20:59,174
And they even left otap. [chuckles]

431
00:20:59,258 --> 00:21:01,718
My sibling and I used to love this.

432
00:21:02,552 --> 00:21:04,388
Ah, really?

433
00:21:04,471 --> 00:21:05,305
[clears throat]

434
00:21:05,389 --> 00:21:07,599
Where is your sibling now?

435
00:21:07,683 --> 00:21:09,977
- Well, I don't know.
- [gentle music playing]

436
00:21:10,060 --> 00:21:11,061
I really don't know.

437
00:21:11,687 --> 00:21:12,729
Okay, thanks.

438
00:21:12,813 --> 00:21:14,439
[in normal voice] Ah, wait.

439
00:21:16,024 --> 00:21:19,319
Do you miss your sibling?

440
00:21:19,903 --> 00:21:21,321
What?

441
00:21:21,405 --> 00:21:23,615
Nothing, uh…

442
00:21:23,699 --> 00:21:25,742
I don't know where she is anymore.
We're not…

443
00:21:25,826 --> 00:21:28,537
Maybe we've forgotten each other.
Let's leave it at that.

444
00:21:29,413 --> 00:21:30,956
[sentimental music playing]

445
00:21:31,039 --> 00:21:32,916
You don't want to see your sibling?

446
00:21:35,919 --> 00:21:38,964
Uh… Wait, why…

447
00:21:39,923 --> 00:21:42,342
Why are you asking so many questions, huh?

448
00:21:42,426 --> 00:21:44,678
Uh, why don't you just come out?

449
00:21:44,761 --> 00:21:46,305
Get out of there.

450
00:21:46,388 --> 00:21:49,516
[sentimental music continues]

451
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:51,768
Oh, Emerson.

452
00:21:53,145 --> 00:21:54,396
Looks like you're lost.

453
00:21:54,479 --> 00:21:56,648
Hmm. Stop it, Atoy.

454
00:21:57,316 --> 00:22:01,695
You're the reason
for the commotion here last night.

455
00:22:01,778 --> 00:22:03,447
What's their beef against you?

456
00:22:05,324 --> 00:22:06,616
[whimsical music playing]

457
00:22:06,700 --> 00:22:08,285
Ah, so that's why you're here?

458
00:22:09,244 --> 00:22:11,830
Well then, you can leave now.

459
00:22:12,581 --> 00:22:14,708
[snickering]

460
00:22:14,791 --> 00:22:15,625
Oh, no.

461
00:22:15,709 --> 00:22:20,964
I bet you messed up
the sizes of their orders, huh?

462
00:22:22,007 --> 00:22:28,764
Or otherwise… you overcharged them, right?

463
00:22:28,847 --> 00:22:31,391
Go ahead. It's free to speculate.

464
00:22:31,475 --> 00:22:33,310
Say whatever you want. It's fine.

465
00:22:33,393 --> 00:22:36,772
So… Do you have anything else to say?

466
00:22:37,773 --> 00:22:41,193
[whimsical music continues]

467
00:22:42,778 --> 00:22:44,780
[snickering]

468
00:22:48,450 --> 00:22:51,244
[music concludes]

469
00:22:56,416 --> 00:22:58,585
- Hey!
- [grunts, chuckles]

470
00:22:58,668 --> 00:23:00,253
[huffs] What's that?

471
00:23:00,337 --> 00:23:02,714
So, you're here. What are you doing there?

472
00:23:02,798 --> 00:23:04,758
Ah, nothing. [chuckles]

473
00:23:04,841 --> 00:23:06,802
Just looking for an order.

474
00:23:06,885 --> 00:23:08,178
Ah.

475
00:23:08,929 --> 00:23:10,222
Uh…

476
00:23:14,309 --> 00:23:15,936
Can you do my makeup again?

477
00:23:17,229 --> 00:23:18,355
Of course.

478
00:23:18,438 --> 00:23:19,856
What's your peg this time?

479
00:23:20,816 --> 00:23:23,693
[thrilling music playing]

480
00:23:25,195 --> 00:23:26,071
That.

481
00:23:28,907 --> 00:23:30,617
- Oh, yes.
- Okay?

482
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:33,537
[electronic blipping]

483
00:23:34,246 --> 00:23:38,416
[intense music playing]

484
00:23:40,502 --> 00:23:43,088
[in English] I cannot wait
to get my hands on Ame.

485
00:23:43,755 --> 00:23:44,756
[in English] I made arrangements already.

486
00:23:44,840 --> 00:23:45,882
[in English] You're gonna have her.

487
00:23:45,966 --> 00:23:47,425
Our fight tonight will be great.

488
00:23:47,509 --> 00:23:49,136
I'm sure you'll enjoy it, sir.

489
00:23:49,219 --> 00:23:50,679
- [Atoy, in English] <i>I really hope so.</i>
- [cheering]

490
00:23:50,762 --> 00:23:52,556
[Atoy, in English] <i>I want</i>
<i>to be entertained.</i>

491
00:23:54,224 --> 00:23:55,851
Sir, please, no!

492
00:23:55,934 --> 00:23:57,144
[crowd cheering]

493
00:23:57,227 --> 00:23:58,353
Darryl!

494
00:23:58,436 --> 00:23:59,604
Whoo!

495
00:23:59,688 --> 00:24:02,149
[in English] Why don't you pick
on somebody your own size?

496
00:24:02,232 --> 00:24:04,276
UP NEXT

497
00:24:04,943 --> 00:24:06,444
- [thuds]
- [grunts]

498
00:24:06,528 --> 00:24:09,364
[in Russian] I'll kill you right here!

499
00:24:09,447 --> 00:24:12,075
[in Russian] You can try!

500
00:24:12,159 --> 00:24:14,870
[intense music continues]

501
00:24:19,332 --> 00:24:21,960
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
